<tr bgcolor="#a0a0a0">
<td>
<p>
<font size=4 color="#700070">
While these are appropriate issues for regulators to address, I confess to
a certain amount of ambivalence about government regulatory processes,
since they can easily be derailed or corrupted by well-financed interests.
It seems to me that the best way t o ensure fairness is to encourage full
participation in the discussion. To that end, I'm concerned less about
whether government regulators or private corporations control the Internet
than I am about making sure the public's interest is represented in th e
decision-making process. We need to monitor our state regulatory
commissions, the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) and Congress. We
also need to put pressure on these institutions to allow for more
democracy in the decision-making process.  <P> And we need to be on guard
if we hope to avoid the sort of future described below by terminally-hip.
</font>
