<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Ecsam</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#008000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#800000" VLINK="#800080"><H1><FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">E.C.S.A.M.</FONT></H1><H2><FONT FACE="Ribbon131 Bd BT"></FONT></H2><H2><FONT FACE="Ribbon131 Bd BT">European</FONT></H2><H2><FONT FACE="Ribbon131 Bd BT"></FONT><FONT FACE="Ribbon131 Bd BT"></FONT></H2><FONT FACE="Ribbon131 Bd BT"><H2>Cyber</H2><H2>Support</H2><H2>All</H2><H2>Music</H2></FONT><H2></H2><HR><H3>1. Who is <FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">E.C.S.A.M.</FONT>?</H3><HR><P></P><H4>Biezeken:</H4><P>Erik Van Biesen ('62)</P><P>Musician, producer and technician</P><P>Studied classical music in his early days, but since about 20 years he played really every genre you can possibly imagine.</P><P></P><H4>Witteken:</H4><P>Luc Heyvaerts ('69)</P><P>Musician, arranger and copywriter</P><P>Studied classical music since the age of eight and has got a degree in it.</P><P>They've  known each other for many years now, and they're playing together in a succesfull band in Belgium (Gorki).</P><HR><P></P><H3>2. What can <FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">E.C.S.A.M. </FONT>do for you?</H3><HR><P>They offer the possibility for bands, musicians, singers, songwriters, record companies, publishers and recording studios to arrange and produce their material in a good European vibe and atmosphere. This means you can have the opportunity to get your recordings to sound like a modern piece of rock 'n roll art, or anyway you wish.</P><P>The last few years a lot of countries (Russia, China, Japan, Korea, etc..) experienced an overwelming growth in popmusic. Especially the European and American music got a breakthrough in these countries .</P><H4>Our method: </H4><P>You send us your<I> audio-information </I>over the Internet, and we'll work it over till it sounds like a genuine European song.</P><P>   <I>Your</I><I> audio-information</I>: a recorded song, an idea, a non-accompaigned vocal, a score, etc..</P><P><I>What we can do with it</I>: your wish is our command (mixdown, remix, record new instruments, mastering service for compact disc, etc..)</P><P>Once this is done, we send you back your music over the Internet (a stereo mix, a stereo mix mastered for compact disc, multi-track, etc..)</P><H4>The advantages of our system:</H4><P>FAST, LOW COST, NO RISK, WORLDWIDE ACCES.</P><P>We eliminate the travel expences and the loss of time, hotel costs, the risk of losing your original tapes, etc..</P><HR><P></P><H3>3. Where is <FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">E.C.S.A.M.</FONT>?</H3><HR><P>In Belgium, a country in between Holland, Germany, France end England.</P><P>According to your budget we choose a recording studio to work your music over.</P><P>Our standard is the DK-studio in Ghent. </P><P>This recording studio has got an MTA-series 980, 64-channel mixing console, an Augan OMX 24 digital 24 track and 3 Alesis ADAT-recorders(24 tracks), both systems can be linked to create a 48 track recording device.</P><P>Analogue and digital mastering recorders, lots of effect-units, a wide range of quality microphones, and all and requirements of a professional sound studio.</P><HR><P>If you want to know more about <FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">E.C.S.A.M</FONT><FONT FACE="Matura MT Script Capitals">. </FONT>, please feel free to contact us.</P>
Just send us an e-mail.<HR></BODY></HTML>
