<HTML>


<HEAD><TITLE>MBTCSENG</TITLE></HEAD>


<BODY><Body bgcolor="#191970" text="#ffffff" link="#ffff00" vlink="#80ffff"><center><IMG SRC="mb4c.gif"><P><Font size=8><B>Tecnical College Slagelse<BR><Font size=6>Denmark<BR><BR><img src="linero2.gif"><BR><BR>Youthstart project:</B><BR><Font size=4><I>(for a <A HREF="mbtcsdan.htm">Danish</A> version ...)</I>
<BR>


<table><td width="600"><font size=4><BR>
<H1>Objectives / goals</H1>

The overall objective of the Youthstart project at The Technical College Slagelse is to develop a new teaching module for the first school period where the use of information technology is integrated as much as possible into all teaching subjects.<BR>
Besides the above goal is to add an international dimension to the first school periods.<BR><BR><BR>

<H1>Activities</H1>

A 20 weeks course dealing with initial vocational training within 4 different areas. The areas and departments involved in the project are:<BR><BR>

<ol><li>The Food Processing Department<li>
The Department for Transport and Logistics<li>
The Agriculure Department<li>
The Iron and Metal Department</ol>

All four departments have developed new courses to both meet the governmental requirements for the first school period and at the same time make new subjects to fulfil the goals of the local Youthstart project - namely to integrate modern information technology into as many teaching activities as possible.<BR><BR>

Basically this means that the participants will work much more with computers and other electronic equipment than students attending regular first school periods. In order to enable the participants to do so classrooms have been fitted with multi-media machines. On request the students can access these classrooms outside regular teaching hours.<BR><BR>

Naturally all four courses have some common core subjects aiming to teach the participants basic skills in connection with working with computers but the contents of the 4 courses are individually designed to meet the needs of the four different vocational areas represented.<BR><BR>

The common core subjects are:
<ul><li>General word and data processing<li>
Creating a home page<li>
Working with "Authorware"<li>
Transfering information/data from one media to another<li>
Using Internet as a means of communication<li>
Information and Internet</ul>

The courses are organised slightly differently at the four different departments but except for The Agricultural Department all departments have chosen to offer potential course participants a sort of "package solution" where they choose to attend a Youthstart class instead of a regular first school period class. At The Agricultural Department the Youthstart class is organised as part of the students optional subjects alongside a range of other optional subjects.<BR><BR><BR>

<H1>Target groups</H1>

<ul><li>Young people in initial-vocational training who have no specific training within the area of working with information technology.
<li>Teachers at Technical Colleges.</ul><BR>

<H1>Contacts</H1>
