<HEAD><TITLE>MBNWI</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY><Body bgcolor="#2f4f2f" text="#ffffff" link="#ffff00" vlink="#80ffff" aLink="#ff0000"><center><IMG SRC="mb5c.gif"><P><font size=7><B>North West Institute<BR>
<Font size=5>of Further and Higher Education<BR><BR>
<font size=4>- Londonderry, N. Ireland -</B><BR><BR>

<table><td width="600"><font size=4><BR>


<H1>Departments:</H1>
<Font size=4>
<ul><li>Arts and General Studies<li>
Business and Management Studies<li>
Caring Services<li>
Construction and Allied Services<li>
Engineering<li>
Mathematics, Science and Computing<li>
Secretarial Studies and Office Arts<li>
Social Education</ul><BR><BR>

<H1>Mediabridge Project:</H1>
The project consists of 2 sections:<BR><BR>

<ul><li>development of multimedia course materials to train young people in understanding some of the issues which they will face when they enter the work place for the first time.
<li>development of a new training course, called Technology Today, covering a wide range of the latest applications of technology.</ul><BR>
<center><H3>SECTION 1</H3></center>

The Institute has realised from research with local industry that many young people entering the world of work for the first time often lack the basic knowledge of the modern businesses environment.<BR><BR>

Often this culture shock means that their positive contribution to their employer is sometimes slower to be realised than hoped by both the new worker and employer.<BR><BR>

The development of these training materials aims to bridge this current shortcoming in most education and training courses. The materials developed consist of a CD ROM based multimedia tool with a supplementary course manual to be retained by the young person.<BR><BR><BR>

<center><H3>SECTION 2</H3></center>

Technology Today training course covers the following areas:<BR><BR>

<ul><li>computer graphics<li>
sound<li>
music<li>
video<li>
developing multimedia materials<li>
using the Internet</ul><BR><BR>

<H2>Target Group</H2>

The target group for the training is unemployed young people aged between 16 and 20 years who have little or no qualifications.<BR><BR><BR>

<P>

<H2>Contact</H2>
Martin Peoples<BR>
North West Institute<BR>
10 Northland Road<BR>
Londonderry<BR>
tel. 44/1504/372136 or 44/1504/311296<BR><BR>

