<H1><B>It doesn't matter much to me</B></H1>
<HR>
<BR>
Strange water all around me<BR>
and cathedrals in my head <BR>
Speechless at the phone and sleepless in my bed<BR>
as I wake tot greet the morning<BR>
Your smell upon my breath
<P>This dark and unknown country<BR>
where I've come to dwell<BR>
has no other drink to offer<BR>
than from your stillborn well<BR>
and This unbridled passion behind those big brown eyes<BR>
covers up a multitude<BR>
of sin behind the lies</P>
<P></P>
<BR>
<B>and it doesn't seem to matter <BR>
if it's Right or wrong<BR>
and it doesnt seem to matter<BR>
even if I know it's wrong<BR>
It doesn't matter much to me<BR>
</B><BR>
<BR>
<P></P>
I'm lost whitout a penny<BR>
and in for more then just a pound <BR>
Wild Wolves around my flesh <BR>
and I can't stand my ground<BR>
I'm bound to end up hurt<BR>
Is this worth to take it on<BR>
as the judge hoists up his gavel<BR>
I'm going, going, gone. 
<P><I>Johan Raedemakers</I></P>
