<head>
<title>Euskadi Information - Short News</title>
</head>

<body>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>

<a name="top"></a>
<table>
<tr>
<td><img align=left width=210 height=120 src="/~euskadi/layout/ei_logo2.gif">
</td>
<td align=center>
<font size=5><b>EUSKADI INFORMATION
<br>
Short News</b></font>
<tt>
<p>
<i>last updated 7. April 1996</i></font></tt></center>
<br>
</td>
</table>

<img align=middle src="/~euskadi/layout/l_rainb.gif">

<p>

<h2>December:</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>02.12.95. THE SENATE'S GAL COMMISSION IS DEAD.</b> 
As announced by the Spanish press on Friday, the Spanish senate's GAL
commission was declared officially dead. Thanks to a PSOE/CiU/PNV alliance,
the most important names in the list of people proposed to testify had been
annulled, and only people with little or no conexion at all with the GAL
affair were approved to appear. PNV leaders like Anasagasti and Ardanza who
have accused Barrionuevo in the GAL affair, and supported an investigation
of Intxaurrondo, decided to side with Felipe Gonzalez and voted in favor
of erasing any crime traces. On 18-Oct, the Spanish senate approved the creation of a special commission to investigate the activities of GAL. Twenty days after, 32 senators were
elected to the senate's GAL commission. On 1-Dec, the senate's commission
was dissolved. More about in <a href="/euskadi/english/e9512.htm">Short News Dec. '95</a>.<p>
<li><b>THE DURANGO BOOK FAIR IN BIZKAIA 6-10 NOVEMBER.</b> 183 stands, 13,280
  books and 996 music records at the most popular Basque book fair.<p>
<li><b>EUSKALTZAINDIA WANTS EUSKARA IN THE BILBO METRO.</b> The Basque academy of
  language Euskaltzaindia expressed his disagreement with the
  treatment of Euskara in the Bilbo Metro. According to Euskaltzaindia,
  it was proven once again the treatment of Euskara as a second rate
  language.<p>
<li><b>CREATED THE AUTODETERMINAZIORANTZ GROUP.</b> In Hegoalde, Aberto Nadal
  and Koldo Goñi founded a group that aspires to become a strong social
  movement pro-self determination in Euskal Herria.  The group has
  already began to make international contacts to gain a wider support.<p>
<li><b>GENERAL RODRIGUEZ GALINDO LOSES CASE AGAINST EGIN.</b> The Donostia Court
  ruled in favor of Basque newspaper Egin and General Galindo will not
  get the 15 million pts he claimed from Egin. Galindo was sueing Egin
  for an information published by the newspaper regarding the narcotraffic
  schemes in Intxaurrondo.<p>
<li><b>PNV JOSEBA EGIBAR SAYS ETA PRISONERS ARE POLITICAL PRISONERS.</b> In an
  interview (29-Nov) with Radio Nacional de España, PNV spokesman Joseba
  Egibar declared that dispersion of ETA prisoners is illegal and that
  has failed. When asked if he considers ETA prisoners as political
  prisoners, Egibar replied that he has no doubt that they are political
  prisoners and added that a state that has 541 prisoners has a political
  problem and that to negate the political base of ETA is to negate what
  it's evident. PP Mayor Oreja accused Egibar of violating the Pacto de
  Ajuria Enea.<p>
<li><b>YOUTH UNEMPLOYMENT IN HEGO EUSKAL HERRIA.</b> According to an INE survey of the
  active population, 51% of Basque youth is unemployed.<p>
</ul>

<hr>
<p>
<h2>Do you want to know more about?</h2>
Read our background informations and detailed news, read what are the propositions for starting with a political dialogue that could lead to a peaceful solution of the conflict, read about our culture and history... Read also an introduction to our <a href="/euskadi/english/e_einfo.htm">alternative information project</a> on the Web. And tell other people about it.
<p>
<hr>

