<p>
<h2><i>Short Introduction</i></h2>
<hr>
<font size=2><tt><center>
Diese Seite ist auch auf <a href="/~euskadi/german/g_einfo">Deutsch</a> vorhanden. Esta página también está a disposición en <a href="/~euskadi/spanish/s_einfo">castellano</a>. Vous pouvez consulter cette page aussi en <a href="/~euskadi/french/f_einfo">français</a>. Horrialde hau <a href="/~euskadi/basque/b_einfo">euskaraz</a> ere ba dago.
</center></tt></font>
<hr>
You are in the english section of 
<a href="/~euskadi/english/e_ekoord">EUSKADI INFORMATION</a>. 
You can inform yourself in <a href="/~euskadi/thatsnew">That's New</a> about the 
latest news, articles, archive contents etc. in several languages on our server. <a href="/~euskadi/agenda/agenda">Agenda</a> shows important meetings and addresses, and includes our preferred <a href="/~euskadi/agenda/weblinks">WebLinks</a>, as well as a <a href="/~euskadi/agenda/pinboard">Pinboard</a> for public messages and anouncements. <a href="/~euskadi/english/e_none">Archive</a> leads you into a continuously growing stock of background informations about history, culture and politics, collections of pictures and a bibliography among many others. In <a href="/~euskadi/org/e_org">Organizations</a> we publish  original communiqués and documents of the different organizations of the Basque National Liberation Movement. <a href="/~euskadi/herria/h_eginez">Herria Eginez</a> is a chronology of events and a selection of several articles and interviews published by the monthly review of Herri Batasuna (in basque and spanish).<br>
We are sorry for not being able to translate quickly all our materials into the different languages. We'll do our best, but you are invited to also have a look to our <a href="/~euskadi/german/g_einfo">german</a> or <a href="/~euskadi/spanish/s_einfo">spanisch</a> pages.

<p>
<img align=middle src="/~euskadi/layout/l_rainb.gif">

