<head>
<title>Euskadi Information - Our Project</title>
</head>

<body>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>

<a name="top"></a>
<table>
<tr>
<td><img src="/~euskadi/layout/ei_logo2.gif" width=210 height=120 align=left>
</td>
<td align=center>
<font size=5><b>EUSKADI INFORMATION<br>
<i>An Alternative Information Project</b></font>
<tt>
<font size=3>
<p>
<i>last updated 7. April 1996</i></font></tt>
<br>
</td>
</table>

<p>
<img align=middle src="/~euskadi/layout/l_rainb.gif">

<p>
<h2>Some thoughts about a new EUSKADI INFORMATION</h2>
<font size=3>
<hr>
<font size=2><tt><center>
Diese Seite ist auch auf <a href="/~euskadi/german/g_ekoord">Deutsch</a> vorhanden. Esta página existe también en <a href="/~euskadi/spanish/s_ekoord">castellano</a>.
</center></tt></font>
<hr>
<p>
<b>Who we are? - A look back</b>
<p>
In 1984 we founded a Solidarity Committee with Euskadi in Zurich, Switzerland. We worked in order to support the people in the Basque Country in its fight for peace, freedom and liberation from all kind of oppression. The spreading of direct information was a main challenge from the beginning: it is still nearly impossible to get objective information - if any - about the situation in the Basque Country. The main printed and tv-news and magazines are biased by a systematic desinformation strategy designed by the spanish Ministery of Interior and translated into practice by well reputed newspapers like EL PAIS and many others.<br>
We published for several year a magazine called EUSKADI INFORMATION, in German, and finished by organizing the EUSKADI KOORDINATION, a kind of loose structure which worked with many other committees, collectives and individuals in Switzerland, Germany and Austria. 1993 was a critical year and we had to give up many of the projects we were working on, mainly due to the lack of financial and human ressources.<p>

<b>Why a new project today? - About the actual situation</b>
<p>
A few years have passed since then, but nothing has really changed. Although new approaches have been made in some conflicts, even if their issue is uncertain yet, the Basque Country is still awaiting a negotiated solution for his historical demands on selfdetermination, peace and freedom. Neither the brutal repression nor the criminalization of the whole liberation movement have broken the activity of ETA, the resistance in the streets and the daily work and mobilization of the numerous popular movements working in all the range from antirepression to culture and language defense.<br>
But not only the spanish PSOE-government, whose President González sinks into the mud of his corruption affaires and the scandal about the paramilitary death-squadrons from the GAL, also the post-franquist opposition from the Partido Popular as well as the basque oligarchy from the PNV are responsible of the <i>status quo</i>. They all try to "pacify" the conflict, through military annihilation or through slow attrition. They are hoping that the radical questioning of the actual social and political system, the big and perseverant demand for a new society and a true selfdetermination - national, but also social, economical and cultural - could be reduced to a insignificant level. Thus, the conflict promises to become even harder, but a lot of basque people don't give up to fight for a free and solidarian Euskadi, for the utopy of a better world after all.<p>
<b>And how further? - An outlook</b>
<p>
Not only for the basque people, its more than 600 political prisoneers and thousands of refugees and tortured, we think that also for other peoples and movements in Europe it is very important that the fight in Euskadi might go on, show some results, and continue to be an obstacle for the actual imperialistic concept of Europe from the EC and a symbol for solidarity for all the others.
So we try to materialize our support through an alternative information project with the old name "EUSKADI INFORMATION". With little means, but - thanks to the electronics of this brave new world - as widespread as possible. We expect that you not only inform yourself throgh this pages, but that you may use what you find here to include it in your own political, social or information work you do. <p>
With solidarian greetings,
<p>
<i>Euskadi Koordination</i>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<h2>Our address is:</h2>
<p>
Euskadi Koordination<br>
Postfach 7323<br>
CH - 8003 Zürich<br>
<p>
<hr>
