<HEAD>

<TITLE>Federation</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="back.jpg">

<H1>The ICYE Federation</H1>

<P>An average of 2000 participants take part in the short-term programmes, study sessions and
visits, training courses, workshops and thematical events on relevant questions in the fields of
international volunteering and global education organized by the ICYE member organisations and
regional structures.</P>

<P>ICYE has a consultative status -category C- with <A
HREF="friends.htm#UNESCO">UNESCO</A> and the UN Economic and Social Council,
fraternal status with the World Council of Churches, is member of the Coordinating Committee
for International Voluntary Service and Mobility International.

</P><P>

Today it manages non-profit long and shortterm intercultural programmes in over thirty countries
worldwide: every year an average of 600 participants, aged between 17 and 25, live abroad from
six to twelve months and cooperate in voluntary social work.  Hosting ICYE national
organisations coordinate the exchanges, running orientation sessions and initial language training,
issue seminars, mid-year and final evaluations and providing the necessary counseling and
support, when needed.

</P>

<HR>

<P><A HREF="noneur.htm">Non-European ICYE programmes </A>are currently operating in:
Bolivia, Brazil, Canada, Colombia, Costa Rica, Ghana, Honduras, India, Japan, Kenya, Mexico,
New Zealand, Nigeria, Sierra Leone, South Korea, Taiwan and the USA.</P>

<P></P>

<P>The International office can be reached at:<BR>

<P></P>

ICYE International Office<BR>

Grosse Hamburger Str. 30<BR>

10115 Berlin<BR>

Germany<BR>

<P></P>

Tel.: (+49) 30 2839 0550<BR>

Fax.: (+49) 30 2839 0552<BR>

E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:icyeio@oln.comlink.apc.org">icyeio@oln.comlink.apc.org</A><BR>

Website: <A
HREF="http://www.wideopen.igc.org/iearn/icye/index.html">www.wideopen.igc.org/iearn/
icye/index.html</A><BR>

<P></P>

<HR>

<CENTER><A HREF="icye.htm"><IMG SRC="earth.gif"><BR>

Home</A><BR>

</P><P>

<EM>Designed by Hans Langouche<BR>

