<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ICYE Europe</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="back.jpg">
<H1>What is ICYE Europe all about ?</H1>
<P>ICYE Europe is the association of the <A HREF="nc.htm">European ICYE National member Organisations</A>.  It was established in 1977 and since 1987 it is an international organisation registered under Belgian law.  ICYE Europe 's aims and purposes, as s

tated in its constitution, are the following:
</P><P>
<CENTER><B>"The purpose of the Association is to facilitate the exchange of young people between nations, as ameans of international, intercultural and economical education and as a means of becoming sensitive to the social, political and economical reali

ties of Europe and the rest of the world."</B></CENTER></P>
<UL>
<LI>implement the purpose of the programme of the Federation of National Committees of the International Christian Youth Exchange;
<LI>support the exchange of young persons between nations, on the basis of long-term and short-term projects;
<LI>be a forum where members share their needs, interests, problems and proposals;
<LI>coordinate the resources of members for their planning, development and financing of the programme of the Association;
<LI>hold seminars about problems and developments related to Europe;
<LI>cultivate new areas of exchange;
<LI>seek financial contributions and grants from organisations, foundations and individuals;
<LI>approach cooperation with European youth and cultural movements.
</UL>
<HR>
<P>
ICYE Europe is member of the Youth Forum of the European Union, of ECB - the European Coordination Bureau of International Youth Organisations and of the Association of Voluntary Service Organisations.  It is contributing to the setting-up of the Common E

uropean Youth Platform, which will result from the merging of the <A HREF="friends.htm#YF">Youth Forum</A>, <A HREF="friends.htm#ECB">ECB</A> and <A HREF="friends.htm#CENYC">CENYC</A> - the Council of European National Youth Committees.
</P><P>
ICYE Europe regularly cooperates with the European Commission in Brussels - in particular with <A HREF="friends.htm#DGXII">Directorate General XXII</A>, responsible for Education, Training and Youth and with the Council of Europe 's European Youth Directo

rate and Centres in Strassbourg and Budapest.
</P><P>
In addition to the programmes in the countries in which member organisations are active, ICYE Europe has been carrying out short-term exchanges also with <A HREF="friends.htm#Partners">partners</A> in Israel, Lithuania, Morocco, Palestine, Tunisia and Tur

key.
</P><P>
The ICYE European Office publishes every two months "Euronews", which updates and reports on the <A HREF="activ.htm">activities</A> of the Association.
</P>
<HR>
