<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Upcoming activities</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="back.jpg">
<H1>Upcoming activities</H1>
<P>This page gives a short overview of the activities we are organizing the following months. 
They are seminars or training courses on different subjects.  People who want to participate, pay a
participation fee that covers a full travel refund, one week of board and lodging, and a program
brought to you by motivated people with a vast experience concerning the handled topics.</P>
<P>If you are interested you can fill in the application form at the bottom of this page or contact
us at <A HREF="mailto:icyeeur@knooppunt.be">icyeeur@knooppunt.be</A> or via our other
coordinates which you can find at the bottom of the <A HREF="icye.htm">first page</A>.</P>
<H2>"Euro-Turkish study visit to Europe"</H2>
<P>
Where: Brussels / Belgium; Strassbourg / France<BR>
Date: January 26, 1997 - February 3, 1997<BR>
Participation fee: 350 DM<BR>
Description:</BR>
This seminar is a study visit to Europe.  It will mainly focus on all the European institutions and
their youth programs.  The visits include DG I, DG XXII and DG VIII at the European
Commission, visit to the European parliament and a session with two European parliamentarians. 
It will also include a visit to Strassbourg to the Council of Europe, the Youth Center, Directorate
and Foundation.  Also included are meetings with the European Youth Forum and some other
international NGO's.
</P>
<H2>"Cultures of Europe"</H2>
<P>
Where: Stockholm / Sweden<BR>
Date: January 26, 1997 - February 2, 1997<BR>
Participation fee: 300 DM<BR>
Description:<BR>
This seminar will focus on cultures in Europe.  What is a culture ?  What different cultures exist in
our society ?  Who is European ?  How do we handle cultural conflicts ?  How do we deal with
culture shocks ?  All these questions are important for people interested in and directly working
with intercultural activities.  The program will include lecturers, working-groups, role-games and
a study visit.<BR>
When exchanging within Europe we often neglect the cultural differences that exist between our
countries and we prejudice our neighbors to be exactly like us ...  With the <bold>EVS</bold>-
program this issue will become even more important.  We will also have practical training on the
<bold>EVS</bold>-procedures which will give all of us that do not know how
<bold>EVS</bold> really works a chance to solve concrete day -to -day problems.</BR></P>


</P>
<HR>
<P>If you are interested in one of these activities, please fill out our <A
HREF="appl.htm">application form</A>.</P>
<HR>
<CENTER><A HREF="icye.htm"><IMG SRC="earth.gif"><BR>
Home</A><BR>
</P><P>
<EM>Designed by Hans Langouche<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:kurdy@dds.nl">kurdy@dds.nl</A></EM></CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
