<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis QS6</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/qs6.jpg">
<h1>64 Voice Expandable Synthesizer</h1>
<hr>



The Alesis QS6 64 Voice Expandable
Synthesizer was designed to provide an
allround synthesis solution for keyboard
players, music composers, and multimedia
authors alike. The QS6 starts with a powerful
64 Voice synth engine for your most complex
MIDI sequences, powered by 8MB of sound
ROM. The QS6's sound library is expandable
to 16MB, either through Alesis QuadraCards
or blank Flash RAM cards for use with our
Sound Bridge sample transfer software. The
QS6 has 640 great sounding programs and
500 multitimbral mixes, induding a complete
bank of sounds in the General MIDI format for
authoring and playback of multimedia sounds.
To help you start creating new music right away, we've included a built-in
serial port for direct interface to a computer, eliminating the need for expensive
MIDI interfaces. There's also a packaged CD-ROM filled with sequencers, editors, song files, and samples which tum the QS6 into a complete music workstation.<p>
<b>With its true 64voice polyphony, huge sonic library of awesome
Programs and Mixes, open-ended expansion capabilities and innovative
computer interface, the QS6 was specifically designed for everyone who
creates synthesized music.</b>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























