<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AKAI DR-8</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/akai.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/dr8.jpg">
<p>
<h1>DR-8 Harddisk-recorder</h1>
<hr><p>
<h2>The Akai DR8 will set free the music which is trapped inside your creative imagination.
Record, edit, play back making full use of the DR8's 8-track potential.  The power of the latest
in digital MTR technology has arrived with a very attractive price!</h2>
<p>

<h2>8-track Digital Simultaneous Recording & Playback<br>
Editing Functions Found Only On Tapeless Machines<br>
Easy 0peration With The Feel Of Analog MTR<br>
16-channel Programmable Mixer Function<br>
</h2>
<hr>
<h4>8-track simultaneous digital recording and playback</h4>
<p>

The Akai DR8 is capable of high-quality 16-bit linear 8-track simultaneous recording and
playback.  The IGB hard disk allows up to 3 hours and 17 minutes of recording time ( 24.625
minutes x 8 tracks at a sampling frequency of 44.1 kHz).<br> The DR8 can have an optional hard
disk installed, or its SCSI port fitted allows the connection to an external hard disk. (Please
consult with Akai dealers or sales outlets for the information on compatible hard disks for use
with the DR8.  The DR8HD has the 1GB internal hard disk installed as standard.) The DR8's
digital interface, another standard feature, allows data recorded on the hard disk to be backed
up to DAT.<br>
ln future upgrades, you will be able to record and play back with the DR8 connected to an
external MO (magneto-optical) disk drive (4-track simultaneous recording/8-channel
simultaneous playback).  What is more, you will be able to simultaneously operate up to
seven DR8s without a synchronizer (separately sold remote cables AL-X50 are required), to
increase the number of tracks to a maximum of 56.<br>
The DR8's flexible expandability and upgradability lets you assemble the system to meet your
individual needs.
<p>

<h4>Convenient editing functions<br>
Zero degradation of sound quality and no loss of original data.</h4>
<p>

The Akai DR8 offers the wide variety of powerful editing functions which maximize the merits
of tapeless and digital technology.  You can edit in ways not possible on digital tape MTR
systems.  The DR8 will let you break down the barriers to produce the music that is inside
you.  No need for fast-forward/rewind because the random access to the recorded data
allows you to instantly edit or play back any sound from any track.  You can copy/move/insert
or erase phrases which extend across multiple tracks, and quickly compile the best music
from all your best takes.<br>
The DR8's TAKE function allows you to record up to five trial recordings.  This is done using
the five TAKE keys on the front panel (TAKE 1-5). You can easily select the best of the five
takes.
The AUTO PUNCH IN/PUNCH OUT function allows you to perform rehearsals.  The DR8
also has a VARISPEED function which is particularly useful for pitch adjustments.<br>
All editing involves digital signal processing so there is no degradation of sound quality.  The
UNDO function lets you go back one step if you make a mistake.  Don't worry if you make a
mistake, just undo and try again!
<p>

<h4>16-channel mixer function</h4>
<p>

The DR8 has a programmable mixer which can mix 8 external channels with 8 internal ones.<br>
The MIX mode allows you to set and record the level, pan, two fx sends, buss ON/OFF, and
can be used in auto-mixing.  Ping-pong recording can be performed on 6 disk tracks and 8
external signals on 2 channels using the buss.
<p>

<h4>CONVENIENT JOG/SHUTTLE.<br>
EASY-TO-SEE KEY LAYOUT.<br>
COMFORTABLE OPERATION WITH THE FEEL OF ANALOG MTR.</h4>
<p>

The DR8's JOG/SHUTTLE control lets you search for and locate your edit
points faster, while listening to the playback.  The 9 Direct Locate points and 100 Stack
points allow you to directly call up edit points.<br>
All the basic MTR function keys are laid out on the upper half of the front panel.  The editing
functions and other controls for detailed work are located on the lower half.  The DR8 control
layout promotes easy operation.
<p>

<h4>ADVANCED, HIGH SOUND QUALITY COMPONENTS</h4>
<p>

<ul>
The DR8 features Akai's own world-acclaimed digital technology and the latest in component
design. The unit has a high-density 18-bit 64-times over-sampling A/D converter and an
advanced 1-bit dual 20-bit D/A converter. The DR8 has the same high level of sound quality
found in professional equipment.
<li>The DR8 has a word clock/ video-sync terminal for digital synchronization.  Optional interface
boards enable synchronization with SMPTE time codes and MIDI sequencers.
<li>An ALESIS ADAT Digital Interface, a future option, will allow digital audio signals to be sent
to and received from ADAT on 8-channels using a single cable.
<li>An RS422 board and a Bi-phase board will be introduced in the future to allow the DR8 to be
integrated into film and video editing environments.
</ul>
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>

















