<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis Quadrasynth 8</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/qs8.jpg">

<h1>64 Voice 88 Key Expandable Master Synthesizer</h1><hr>

The QS8 64 Voice
88 Key Expandable
Master Synthesizer
is the new flagship
of the Alesis keyboard
line. By combining all
the advantages of an
incredibly powerful,
full-size master con
troller with a highly-
advanced synthesis
engine, the QS8
offers the perfor
mance you expect
from a professional
quality keyboard
instrument. It fea
tures an 88-key weighted hammer-action keyboard, offering the expressive feel
that can only be compared to a fine acoustic piano. The QS8 incorporates 16
megabytes of onboard sound  ROM, featuring a new phase-accurate stereo
grand-piano as well as a full complement of organs, strings, drum, percussion, brass, woodwinds, rhythmic/sonic loops, and several banks of both new and classic synth textures. The QS8 offers 640 great-sounding, very usable Programs and 500 multitimbral Mixes, which may be expanded to 1792 Programs and 1400 Mixes (32Mb of ROM) using its two PCMCIA sound card slots and Alesis Quadracards.<p>
In addition to the aftertouch and release velocity features of its keyboard, the QS8's extensive master controller features include four fully-assignable real-time control sliders as well as pitch and modulation wheels.A sustain pedal jack and two assignable pedal inputs are provided on the rear panel. The QS8 also implements the powerful QS modulation matrix, allowing users to assign virtually any controller source to any modulation parameter. The onboard effects processor utilizes four totally discrete effects busses for powerful reverb, delay, rotary speaker simulation, distortion, chorus and much more. Plus, using Alesis' new Sound
Bridge 2.0 software and any Mac or PC, the QS8 can import AIFF and .WAV samples as well as Standard MIDI Files and program data, and store the information to
PCMCIA Flash or SRAM cards. Standard MIDI file sequences can then be played back by the QS8 without the use of any external sequencing device.<p>
For direct digital connection to ADAT recorders and compatible products, the QS8 includes the ADAT optical Digital output. Also featured is a serial data port that provides direct connection to a Macintosh or PC without a MIDI interface. Four independent 1/4" audio outputs are also provided. The QS8 includes a CD-ROM in Mac and Windows format that includes Steinberg's Cubase lite, Alesis' new Sound Bridge 2.0 and Freloader software, General MIDI sequences, sound editor/librarians, additional sample and program data and other third party software. Its strong all-metal chassis includes black solid oak endpieces for support and is designed for use both in studiois and on the road.<p><b> If you're a professional keyboardist, the powerful synthesis features and incredible controller functions of the QS8 make it the ultimate tool for music composition and performance.</b>
<hr>
