<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Ensoniq ASR</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ensoniq.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/asr.jpg">
<p>
<h1>ADVANCED SAMPLING RECORDERS</h1>
<hr><p>
<h2>FEATURES</h2>
<ul>
<li>Choice of 88-key weighted or 61-key synth action keyboards, or rack version
<li>Up to 31 voice polyphony
<li>Up to 16 MB memory
<li>Stereo sampling at 44.1 and 29.76 kHz
<li>Analog or digital input
<li>Sampling through effects
<li>Advanced resampling
<li>Imports Rolandlm and AkaiTMCD-ROM's
<li>24-bit effects processor with 62 algorithms (248 preprogrammed variations)
<li>Virtual 16-track sequencer
<li>"Play While Load"
<li>Bank loading of complete performance setups (including sequencer data)
<li>Easy sound layering and splitting
<li>HD disk-drive/optional SCSI (SP-3)
<li>Up to 8 polyphonic outpu
<li>Patch Select buttons
<li>Optional digital I/O (DI-10)
</ul>
<hr><p>
<h2>It's More than a Sampler.</h2>Keyboard or rackmount, the ASR-10 and ASR-88 Advanced
Sampling Recorders provide you with a complete digital production studio.  These high-
quality samplers integrate an effects processor, a MIDI sequencer, and a digital tape recorder
all in one easy-to-use instrument.<br><br>
<b>An ASR For Every Need</b> - Only ENSONIQ offers samplers in different configurations; our
polyphonic pressure synth action ASR-10 keyboard, the rack ASR-10, and our newest 88-key
weighted action ASR-88.  The ASR-88 comes complete with 16 MB RAM, SCSI, a CD-ROM
drive, and two free CD-ROM discs - a completely expanded system, ready to use right out of
the box!
<p>

<b>Sampling</b> - Create stunning 16-bit samples in stereo or mono, with up to 16 MB of sample
memory.  Then, shape your sounds using the ASR's extensive voice architecture and editing
features.
<p>

<b>Effects Processing</b> - The ASR has the most powerful onboard effects processor ever offered
in a sampler.  Sixty-two effects algorithms (from our acclaimed DP/4) offer many creative
possibilities.  You can sample through effects such as EQ or compression to condition your
sound upon input, or resample a sound multiple times through different effects.  You can even
process external audio through the ASR while you play live or play back sequences,
eliminating the need for added gear.
<p>

<b>Sequencing</b> - No mere scratchpad, the ASR's 16-track sequencer provides real time and
looped recording modes, 96 PPQ clock resolution, an auto-locate function, and many of the
same advanced, yet easy-to-use features that have made ENSONIQ keyboards famous
around the world!
<p>

<b>Digital Audio Recording</b> - Add two tracks of live audio performance to your MIDI sequenced
tracks for complete music production with one instrument.  Record to RAM or SCSI hard drive
with the simplicity of a tape-recorder, with advanced features like punch-in/out, and
auditionable editing.  No other sampler gives you this extraordinary capability.
<p>

<b>Access to Sounds</b> - The best library of sounds available, including both floppy disk and CD-
ROM volumes.
For access to the broadest range of sounds, the ASR also imports AkaiTM (S-100011100)
and Roland TM CD-ROM's, complete with programming and performance parameters!  A
high-density (HD) disk drive is standard, while the SP-3 SCSI interface (optional on the ASR-
10 keyboard; standard on the ASR-88 keyboard and the ASR-10 rack) supports using up to
seven simultaneous hard disks and/or CD-ROM drives.
<p>

<b>The Best Supported Sampler</b> Since its release, we have continually enhanced the ASR-10 -
adding digital audio recording, digital 1/0 support, importing of new sound formats, and more. 
Best of all, we've made each new release available free to our users!
<p>

<h4>It's no wonder the ASR is the best-selling sampler in the music industry!</h4>
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Keyboard and Rack Versions</h2>
The ASR is available in synth action,
weighted action, and rackmount versions.
All versions offer the same advanced sampling capabilities, high-quality effects, expressive
performance features, integrated sequencing, and digital audio recording.<br>
The 61-key synth action Poly-KeyTm ASR-10 keyboard has polyphonic pressure sensitivity for
added nuance with each note.  A SCSI-equipped version of the keyboard is also available,
and you can add 6 more polyphonic outputs to the keyboard with the OEX-6sr output
expander.  The rackmount ASR-10 comes standard with SCSI and 8 outputs.<br>
The ASR-88 offers our acclaimed 88-key weighted action piano keyboard with a variety of
velocity curves designed to match your playing style, channel aftertouch, fully expanded
memory (16 MB), SCSI, and a bundled 2x CD-ROM drive with two free discs.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Advanced Sampling Capabilities</h2> The ASR-10 and ASR-88 have 8 Instrument locations and
hold up to 16 MB of RAM.  Record and play back long samples, or just fill up the ASR with
great sounds from our extensive sound library.<br><br>
<b>Sampling</b> - The ASR offers stunning 16-bit stereo sampling at 44.1 or 29.76 kHz sampling
rates.  You can sample dry or through the onboard effects processor.  This lets you condition
the sound upon input, or add creative coloring to your loops and special effects.<br>
You can also sample external audio while the sequencer is playing.  Jam along with your
sequenced tracks: your singing or playing will be recorded perfectly in time.<br>
For the highest quality sampling from CD or DAT, use the optional DI-10 digital input (SIPDIF
digital interface).   However you sample, hardware envelopes and high-quality output circuitry
ensure absolutely noise-free playback.<br><br>
<b>Sound Programming</b> - The ASR's extensive voice architecture gives you total control over
your sound.  Edit your samples using a wide variety of DSP commands, with 5 types of
auditionable cross-fade looping, gain normalization, timestretching, auto looping, and more.<br>
Up to 127 samples are placed into each Layer, for detailed multi-sampling or placing a
different sound on every key.<br>
With 8 Layers available per Instrument, the ASR provides a variety of ways to combine
samples into expressive sounds.  WaveSamples can be stacked and detuned against each
other for rich layers and sound combinations.  Up to 8 different samples can be velocity cross-
switched/faded to create amazingly lifelike drum kits or responsive acoustic instruments. 
Layers can be triggered when you release a key for realistic guitar strumming, doublepicking,
and other special effects.<br>
With our exclusive Patch Select buttons you can call up 4 different combinations of Layers,
which can be
programmed for different performance nuances or sound combinations.  Emulate acoustic
instrument characteristics, access parameter variations, or even call up completely different
sounds.<br><br>
<b>Resampling</b> - The ASR can resample existing sounds - digitally combining multiple sounds
into one new stereo or mono sample.  Repeatedly resample a sound, with a different effect
each time, to create a multi-effects processed sound.  Resample the Main Outputs to create
hip audio loops from riffs, drum grooves, vocal phrases, or entire multi-track sequences. 
Resample your drums to add individual effects to each drum, and then add a global effect to
create the perfect final mix.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Professional Onboard Effects</h2>
The ASR's 24-bit effects processor has 62 algorithms (50 in ROM, 12 on O.S. disk), each
with 4 preprogrammed variations, giving you 248 different presets.  This selection was
carefully designed to cover most processing needs simply select the variation you want and
get to work.<br>
Every algorithm offers a comprehensive selection of parameters, rivaling many high-end
signal processors.  Each
effect can respond to 2 modulation sources, for real-time control of the effects mix, delay
times, reverb damping, or any other possible parameter.<br>
The Audio Tracks control lets you use the effects processor for live performance.  Sing
through the ASR while playing its keyboard, or play guitar through onboard effects along with
presequenced accompaniment tracks.  There's no need for any additional gear!
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Digital Audio Recording</h2>
Audio Tracks give you two tracks of digital audio recording to combine live audio with your
sequenced tracks.  Add whatever live audio you wish - sing, play guitar, blow your horn - using
Audio Tracks the way you would use tape.<br>
Audio Tracks can be recorded in two ways:
<ul>
<li>RAMTracks - Record to internal memory with no additional hardware.
<li>DiskTracks - Record direct to hard disk via SCSI.  Recording time is limited only by the
hard disk size.
</ul>

<i>(Both methods work with standard 2 MB memory.  Expanded RAM is recommended to take
full advantage of this feature.)</i><br><br>
Record your performance and then edit the take as needed.  Simply locate to any bar and
punch-in to overdub new material, without any audible glitches.  Bounce-down tracks digitally,
freeing up tracks for unlimited multi-track recording.  Best of all, you can audition your punches
and bounce-downs, so you can compare takes before saving your work.<br>
Use the onboard effects processor any time during Audio Track recording.  Finally, use the DI-
10 digital 1/0 to transfer your mix to DAT, and share your hit with the world!<br>
Use Audio Tracks to produce demos, soundtracks, jingles, radio spots, voice-overs, or to
enhance your live performances.  The ASR is the only sampler (or MIDI instrument, for that
matter) that combines sequencing and digital audio recording.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Sound Support and Storage</h2>
ENSONIQ has a reputation for creating outstanding sound libraries, with many top artists,
engineers, and studios helping to create these libraries.  Our sound designers use many
proprietary tools for creating expressive sounds that continually push the boundaries of
sampling technology.<br>
ENSONIQ Sound Libraries cover many different styles of music.  They are available in two
formats: floppy disks (including new AS Series collections, and our 'Signature Series" sounds
from top artists), as well as our growing library of CD-ROM discs.  Many other companies
support ENSONIQ samplers, with new titles available every month.  Using an SP-3 SCSI
interface for hard disk and CD-ROM access gives the benefits of fast and easy sound loading
- instantly locate any sound with a 4-digit direct dial number - and macros for easily moving
around on your storage device.<br>
Our Version 3 Operating System adds access to Akai (S-1000-1100) and RolandTm sounds
from CD-ROM and SCSI drives.  Unlike other samplers, the ASR converts not only the wave
data, but most of the program parameters as well, so imported sounds are ready to play right
away.  Since sounds are automatically converted to ASR format, you can save them  to your
hard drive, or even edit them if you like.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Powerful Sequencing</h2>
The ASR's 16-track sequencer utilizes a unique sequence/song track structure which lets you
record 8 tracks of music in a Sequence, and then combine multiple sequences into a Song. 
Once you have created the Song form, you can record an additional 8 tracks of overdubs to
smoothly span transitions from sequence to sequence, or to solo over the complete form.<br>
Exceptionally easy to use, the sequencer offers a variety of editing functions including event-
editing, quantization, track transposition, clockshifting, mixing, panning, and more.  And, as
with any ENSONIQ sequencer, you can audition your edits before permanently changing your
data.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>Versatile Performance Features</h2>
It's easy to create splits and layers
on the ASR.  By simply 'double-clicking' an Instrument button you can combine up to 8
Instruments - with control over volume, panning, key ranges, transposition, Patch Select status,
and effects bus routing for each.  You can save up to 8 of these sound combinations as
Performance Presets, available at the push of a button.<br>
ENSONIQ's 'Bank' concept gives you any easy way to store and recall a complete setup for a
specific performance situation or composition.  A Bank is a file that automatically recalls up to
8 Instruments from any number of floppy disks or SCSI devices, all sequence data, your global
effects setting, and your Performance Presets - a simple way to stay organized and save
time!<br>
<h3>With this level of sound and performance control, the ASR isn't simply a recording device - it's
an expressive musical instrument.  Whether you produce rap or hip-hop dance tracks, perform
classical concertos, or blow hot jazz, ENSONIQ has an ASR instrument that will find an
important place in your music.</h3>

<hr>

<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>
















