<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Ensoniq DP/4+</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ensoniq.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/dp4.jpg">
<p>
<h1>Parallel Effects Processor DP/4+</h1>
<hr><p>
<b>Are your effects processing needs growing faster than your budget?</b><br>
To the rescue - the DP/4+ Parallel
Effects Processor. Four independent stereo effects processors integrated into a 2U rack space, for the
utmost in flexibility, functionality, and fidelity.
<p>

Four balanced (TRS) inputs can process from 1 to 4 separate signals. For I input (like your guitar), you can
use all 4 processors to create an amazing sound - rivaling those expensive custom rigs you've dreamed
about. Route 2 or 3 different signals to the DP/4+ and divide the processors between them. Finally, you
can use a single processor for each of 4 separate input signals for maximum flexibility.
<p>

Your output choices are just as flexible. Our advanced mixing scheme lets you maintain signal
independence or mix signals together into 1 or 2 stereo fields. You can even use the DP/4+ as 4 mono
in/stereo out processors!
<p>

Still, all this wouldn't mean much if the DP/4+ didn't sound so good, or come with the effects you need.
First, we improved the audio circuitry for even cleaner performance. We've kept the same 46 algorithms
that critics raved about in the original DP/4, and added some powerful new ones (like 2 dynamic tube amp
algorithms for a natural guitar sound that gets dirtier as you play harder, a guitar tuner, additional guitar
amps and effects, and even a vocal "remover"). In total you've got 54 algorithms designed for the highest
fidelity and the most control over your sound possible.
<p>

Ground-compensated inputs and outputs, and a +4/-10 dB switch provide better signal matching to your
other gear. A front-panel combination XLR/l/4" input gives you easy access even when the DP/4+ is in a
rack. And a headphone jack with signal soloing allows you to tweak your sound in private, or practice your
guitar amp-free!
<p>

We first developed this signal processing concept in the DP/4, which has won critical acclaim and awards
around the world. It's been used on countless records, film scores, TV shows, and live concerts, by a
veritable "who's-who" of top artists and engineers. Now we've made it even better - for guitar players,
home studios, and professional use.
<p>

<b>The DP/4+ Parallel Effects Processor. The one-of-a-kind processor designed to meet the demands of
today's recording and performing artist.</b>
<p>

<hr><p>

<h3>Algorithms</h3>
The DP/4+ has 54 algorithms, as shown in the accompanying table. Eleven types of reverb cover a range
of ambient spaces, from different size rooms and halls, to plates and a P/4+variety of modern reverb effects
as well. Delays up to 6.6 seconds can be sync'd to MIDI clocks or to a triggered Tap Tempo.
<p>

Use the selection of rich, multivoiced chorusing, phasing, flanging, and combination effects to color your
sound. A rotating speaker algorithm captures all the nuances of a Leslie TM speaker.A built-in LFO allows
the DP/4+ to create vibrato, panning, tremolo, and other effects. You can even use the Sine/Noise
generator to create incredible sound effects with no source plugged in at all.
<p>

Guitar players will find a variety of authentic amp and speaker simulations. Our new Dynamic Tube Amp
captures the true character of a real tube amplifier being overdriven. Play quietly and your sound is as clean
as you like; dig in and it becomes gradually more distorted - and you have complete control over the 'feel"
of the change.
<p>

There are 2 dynamic VCF-Distortion algorithms for great wah-wah pedal effects, and even a built-in guitar
tuner! Want to keep playing while you switch effects? The DP/4+ offers "seamless" switching of effects
from the front panel, foot switch, or MIDI Program Change (quickly crossfading from one effect, to dry, to
the new effect) without cutting out your audio signal.
<p>

In the studio, 4 different pitch shifters, a variety of expanders, shelving and parametric EQ's, a
Ducker/Gate, an ultra-fast compressor, and even our new vocal 'remover" provide all the processing tools
needed for record, broadcast, and video production work.
<p>

Each algorithm in the DP/4+ can be modulated in real-time by any 2 of 138 possible MIDI or analog
controllers. For automated control, use MIDI Program Changes to change Presets or to completely change
your DP/4+ setup.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h3>Preset Memory</h3>
With 400 Presets the DP/4+ offers a vast selection of pre-programmed sound processing choices. There
are 4 types of Presets, with 100 memory locations available for each type (50 in read-only memory, 50 in
editable RAM):
<ul>
<li>1 Unit -1 fully programmed algorithm 
<li>2 Unit - 2 combined algorithms
<li>4 Unit - 4 combined algorithms
</ul>

These Presets can be used individually, or as building blocks to create a Config Preset - a global Preset
which stores a complete DP/4+ setup (including input signal routing and all applicable Unit Presets).
<p>
<hr><p>

<h3>Configurations</h3>
With 4 powerful multi-effects processors and a 4-input/4-output patch bay, the DP/4+ can handle any
mixing or live sound situation. The four types of configurations (called Configs) are based on how many
different inputs are used:
<p>

<ul>
<li><b>1 Source Config</b> - Plug in 1 mono or stereo source and use all 4 Units to create a richly effected sound.
For
example, create a refined sound for a vocal track by chaining together an EQ-Compressor, De-esser, Pitch
Shifter, and a Plate Reverb. Or, plug in your guitar and combine a Dynamic Guitar Amp, Speaker
Simulator, EQ-Chorus-DDL, and Reverb - for a sound that can range from an expressive blues lead to an
arena-rocking metal overdrive.
<li><b>2 Source Config</b> - The DP/4+ becomes 2 independent 2-Unit stereo processors. Put EQ Phaser-DDL and
Plate Reverb on your synths while adding Pitch Shift-DDL and Hall Reverb to your band's PA. In a mixing
situation, create a stunning drum sound by combining Room and Non-Lin Reverbs for the bass and snare
drums, and process the toms and cymbals with a combination of Plate and Hall Reverbs.
<li><b>3 Source Config</b> - Use the mixing strength of the DP/4+ to process 3 sources: 2 mono and 1 stereo. You
might use this configuration to add Gated Reverb to your drum machine, Phaser-DDL to an analog synth
and still have 2 Units able to handle stereo vocals.
<li><b>4 Source Config</b> - In this setup you have a rack full of processors ready to handle any mixdown or
broadcast production need. Whether you need 4 Parametric EQ's, multiple Compressors, or a selection of
different Reverbs, Delays, and other effects, you can route 4 mono sends into the DP/4+ and get one or
two B -2 mixed stereo returns!
</ul>
<p>
<hr><p>

<h3>Using The DP/4+</h3>
As powerful as it is, the DP/4+ is actually very easy to use. Here's how:
<ul>
<li>Choose an input configuration based on how many instruments/ sources you want to process (1,2,3, or 4)
<li>Select an effect (or group of effects) for each of the sources
<li>Adjust the effects and routings (if needed) to suit your taste</ul>
If you come across a setting, or group of effects that you want to keep for future use, you can save it as a
Preset any time during your session.
<p>

<hr><p>
<h3>Connectivity</h3>
The DP/4+ has balanced (TRS) 1/4" inputs and outputs for quieter integration into your setup. Ground-

compensated connection guarantees the best signal with the correct gain stage no matter what you connect
it to. The front panel has a combination XLR/l/4" input for your microphone or guitar, and a Gain Adjust
button to select between balanced and line-level signals.
<p>

You'll appreciate the front panel headphone jack, with an output mute button that solo's what you're
listening to in the phones (by disabling the rear panel outputs). Tweak your sound without muting your
mixing board, or quietly practice your guitar - as if your favorite amp was right there!
<p>
<hr><p>
<h3>Interface</h3>
Dedicated input and output volume knobs provide instant access to each of the 4 channels. 3-stage
signal/peak indicator LED's for each input help you optimize signal levels. Each Unit has a dedicated button
to select it for loading Presets, editing, or bypassing. Parameter value changes are easy with the large Data
Entry Knob, and a Compare button allows you to audition your current edit against the stored settings.
Configuration LED's always show your current input setup.
<p>

The DP/4+'s large, 32-character back-lit display provides clear information, and also acts as a gain-
reduction meter during compression modes - a must for critical studio applications. An additional large 2-
character LED shows the currently selected edit parameter, and also acts as a MIDI indicator to confirm
MIDI reception.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h3>Simply the Best</h3>
The original DP/4 set new standards for what an effects processor could and should do. The new DP/4+
adds many of the features that our users have requested, plus a few ideas of our own.
<p>

Best of all, it retains the great sound that helped the DP/4 find its way onto so many hit records, TV and
film scores, and stages around the world. With the new DP/4+, the best has gotten even better.
<p>
<hr><p>
<h2>FEATURES</h2>
<ul>
<li>4 independent 24-bit stereo processors
<li>4 inputs & 4 outputs (balanced 1/4" TRS)
<li>Able to process 1, 2, 3, or 4 signals
<li>54 algorithms
<li>400 Presets
<li>Seamless switching of effects
<li>Dynamic MIDI control
<li>Front-panel headphone jack (with output muting)
<li>Front-panel XLR / 1/4" input
<li>Dedicated input & output volume knobs
<li>3-step input LED's
<li>+41-10 dB switching
<li>Output mixing
</ul>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>




