<html>
<head>
<title>KORG X5d</title>
</head>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<body>

<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/korg.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/x5d.jpg"><br>
<h1>KORG X5D</h1>
<hr>

<b><h3>The Korg X5D, with its great sounds, professional qualities and visionary functions,
offers everything you would expect from a first-class synthesizer. It's very easy to operate though,
and is therefore an ideal instrument for synthesizer-newbies. Compared to the competitors in his
range, the X5D outperforms them all.</h3></b>

<p>
<FONT size="+1">
Future-oriented lay-out and fantastic sounds qualify the X5D for the top-range.
</FONT><br>

In the X5D, all functions of the great X5DR are integrated. It works with the world-famous AI²
Syntehsis System, which also generates the great sounds of the 01/W- and X-series, and which
offers you an incredible 8Mb of PCM-waveforms, giving it a sound-potential that no other synth in
its price-range matches.<br>
The X5D has 430 multisounds and 215 drum/percussionsounds, and 64-voice polyphony, with
which you can realise even the most complex passages in your music.<br>
The two fully independent multi-effect-processors include 47 effect-types, including Delay, Reverb,
Distortion and Rotary Speaker, enabling you to create the exact effect.</body>
<hr>
<FONT size="+1">
Impressive Program/Combination-possibilities plus top-quality sounds for the most demanding
uses.
</FONT><br>

With the X5D, you can store up to 100 new-created programs and combinations. It comes equipped
with classic Korg-sounds from the M1, the T-series, the Wavestation and the 01/W, and offers the
flexibility of 2 program-banks:<i> Preset A</i>, with 100 X5DR-compatible
Programs/Combinations, and <i>Preset B</i>, with 100 X5-compatible Programs/Combinations.
And, because of the freedom of choice between both banks, the X5D offers a wide range of
extraordinary full and expressive sounds. On top of that: the X5D is General-Midi compatible, with
128 GM-programs plus 1 GM-compatible  Drum Programs and 7 others, with which you can
easily play song-data in GM-format.
<hr>
<FONT size="+1">
Practical functions and outstanding features.
</FONT><br>

The X5D comes equipped with 61 keys and both a pitch-bend and a modulation-wheel, which are
indispensible for expressive musical performances. And for musicians who want to play classic or
ethnic music in theit authentic tuning, the X5D offers a special scaling-function, enabling -apart
from the common scales- Werckmeister III, Kirnberger III and Arab, Indonesian and other exotic
tunings.
<hr>
<FONT size="+1">
Compact and light-weight, ideal for live-performances or Multimedia-applications.
</FONT>

In spite of its compact and light construction, the X5D is a full-grown synthesizer, convincing both
on stage and in the studio due to its fascinating sounds. Thanks to its mobility and special qualities,
you can set it up everywhere, immediately, even for jam-sessions.<br>
Furthermore: since it has an integrated PC-interface, you can directly connect it to a PC (Cables
and drivers not included). This way, you can easily take advantage of its 64-voice-polyphony, of
the integrated GM-compatibility, and use its GM-compatible programs direct from your computer,
for playing, editing or recording to your software-sequencer. Mac-compatibility is guaranteed. At
the same time, you will acknowledge that the X5D is the ideal keyboard for both multuimedia and
computer-music.

<hr>
<FONT size="+1">
TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS
</FONT><br>

<ul>
<li>Sound Generation Method: AI² (Advanced Integrated) Synthesis System
<li>Sound Source Access:<ul>
<li>32 voices, 64 oscillators (Double Modus)
<li>64 voices, 64 oscillators (Single Modus)
</ul>
<li>61-key velocity-sensitive keyboard
<li>Waveforms: 8Mb PCM
<li>Effects: 2 digital multi-effects, 47 programs
<li>Program/Combination: <ul>
<li>128 ROM-programs, 8 Drum-programs (1 GM)
<li>100 RAM-programs + 100 Combinations
</ul>
<li>Outputs: L/mono, R, headphones
<li>Midi in, out, thru
<li>Display: backlit LCD (16 X 2)
<li>Power: 12V DC, 700 mA (adaptor included)
<li>Software: bonus-disk SED-00 for Windows/Mac (X5/05 SoundEditor, MIDI driver)
<li>Dimensions: 900 (W) X 254,2 (D) X 83,4mm (H)
<li>Weight: 4,5 Kg
</ul>
<hr>
The X5D is also available as a 9,5"-module (X5DR)
<hr>
