Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="COL29056.ASC"

                        Case COL 290596
                              =20
The International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS-Torture requests
your intervention in the following situation in Colombia.

Brief description :
Central Unitaria de Trabajadores de Colombia (CUT), member of
the network, has informed the International Secretariat that
on the night of 24 May 1996, at 10.00 pm, in the city of
Medell=EDn, an attack caused the death of Guillermo Tobon
Rivera, a 28 year old worker at the Frontino Gold Mines,
father of a young child and treasurer of the National Workers
Union (Sindicato Nacional de Trabajadores) for the Mines and
Energy Industry, SINTRAMIENERGETICA.

According to the information, on the same day a man allegedly
implicated in a previous massacre which took place at the
FUTRAN Regional Federation headquarters, entered the premises
without being stopped or questioned by security.

The information reports that in the same week, some days
earlier, another CUT affiliate was killed, Mr David Flores, in
the city of Cucuta.

Action requested :
Please write to the Colombian authorities urging them to :

i.  guarantee the life as well as the physical and
    psychological integrity of all Colombian citizens, in
    particular take measures to safeguard CUT affiliates;

ii. carry out an exhaustive and impartial investigation into
    the alleged facts - in particular the assassinations of
    Guillermo Tob=F3n Rivera and David Flores, in order to
    identify those responsible, bring them to trial in a
    civilian court and apply the penal, civil and/or
    administrative sanctions in accordance with the law;

iii.ensure the full respect of human rights and fundamental
    freedoms in the country, in accordance with national laws
    and international standards.

Addresses :
S.E.  Dr.  Ernesto Samper Pizano, Presidente de la  Republica,
Palacio  de Narino, Santafe de Bogota, Colombia.  Fax (+  571)
284 21 86 o/or 287 7939
Dr.  Orlando  V=E1squez  Velasquez,  Procurador  General  de  la
Nacion,  Carrera 5, N=BA 15-80, Santafe de Bogota. Fax  (+  571)
284 04 72 o/or 281 7531
Dr.  Carlos Vicente de Roux, Consejero Presidencial  para  los
Derechos  Humanos,  Palacio  de  Narino,  Santafe  de  Bogota,
Colombia.  Fax (+ 571) 341 03 64 o/or 341 8364
Brigadier  General Rozo Jose Serrano Cadena, Director  General
de  la Polic=EDa, Centro Administrativo Nacional CAN, Santafe de
Bogota. Fax (+ 571) 269 58 58
Dr. Horacio Serpa Uribe, Ministro del Interior, Ministerio del
Interior,  Carrera  8a,  No.8-9, Piso 7,  Santafe  de  Bogota,
Colombia.
Telex : 45406 MINGO CO - Fax (+571) 251 58 84
Dr. Alfonso  Valdivieso Sarmiento, Fiscal General. Fax  (+571)
    288 2828

Geneva, 29 May 1996
Kindly inform us of the action undertaken by quoting the code
on the present appeal.

