                        Case COL 100696

The International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS-Torture requests your
URGENT
intervention in the following situation in Colombia.

Brief description of the situation

The   Corporation  of  Lawyers,  member  of  the  network,  has
expressed  its concern for the personal safety and  liberty  of
Sr.  Juan  Manuel  BERNAL GUTIERREZ, an indigenous  student  of
mechanical engineering.

According to reports on June 4 1996, during a peaceful  student
demonstration at the National University, police agents entered
the    university   campus   with   armoured    cars,    firing
indiscriminately.  During this operation an unidentified  woman
student  was  wounded by gunshot and nine other  students  were
detained,  including Juan Manuel BERNAL GUTIERREZ, a member  of
the   indigenous   community  of  Chenche   Amayarco   of   the
municipality of Coyaina.

Although  8 students were released, BERNAL GUTIERREZ  is  still
detained  and held at the disposal of the regional jurisdiction
and of the public order services, in spite of the fact that the
Constitution   provides  for  special  treatment   of   persons
belonging to indigenous groups.

The International Secretariat of OMCT would like to recall that
regional or public order justice has repeatedly been accused of
being  a  secret  procedure with no  real  guarantees  for  the
accused and favouring repeated violations of human rights.

Action requested :

Please write to the Colombian authorities urging them to:

i.  ensure  in all circumstances  respect for the physical  and
    psychological  intgegrity of Juan Manuel  BERNAL  GUTIERREZ
    and  order  his immediate release in the absence  of  valid
    legal  charges against him, or, should such charges  exist,
    bring  him  before  a competent civil tribunal  which  will
    render  a  verdict  in accordance with  the  rules  of  due
    process;

ii. guarantee a thorough and impartial investigation  into  the
    facts  alleged  in  order  to identify  those  responsible,
    bring  them  before a competent  court and impose  on  them
    the  penal, civil and/or administrative sanctions  provided
    by law;

iii.ensure   that   the  injured  persons  receive  appropriate
    medical  assistance and guarantee their right  to  adequate
    compensation;

iv. ensure  the  effective  respect  of  human  rights  and
    fundamental   freedoms  throughout   the   country   in
    accordance   with   national  laws  and   international
    standards.

Addresses :

     S.E.  Dr.  Ernesto  Samper  Pizano,  Presidente  de  la
Republica,  Palacio de Narino, Santafe de Bogota,  Colombia.
Fax (+ 571) 284 21 86

     Dr. Orlando Vasquez Velasquez, Procurador General de la
Nacion, Carrera 5, N=BA 15-80, Santafe de Bogota. Fax (+  571)
284 04 72 o/or 342 97 23

     Dr. Carlos Vicente de Roux, Consejero Presidencial para
los  Derechos Humanos, Palacio de Narino, Santafe de Bogota,
Colombia.  Fax (+ 571) 341 83 64

     Dr. Jaime Cordoba Trivino, Defensor del Pueblo, Fax  (+
571) 346 12 25

      Colombian   diplomatic  missions  in  your  respective
countries.

Geneva, 10th of June 1996

Kindly  inform  us  of any action undertaken quoting  the  code
number of the present appeal in your reply.

--=====================_834588441==_
