                         Case CRI 100696
                               =20
The  International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS-Torture requests  your
URGENT intervention in the following situation in Costa Rica.

Brief description of the situation

Reports  received from CODEHUCA, member of the network,  indicate
that  on  May  30 1996, in the Finca El Achiote, municipality  of
Puerto  Viejo de Sarapiqui, approximately 46 families,  some  150
persons, most of them women and children, were violently attacked
by  police  forces.  As  a  result three people  received  bullet
wounds,  among them Juan Victor Victor, wounded in  the  abdomen,
and  Rene  Rojas, who was hit in the ankle and suffered fractures
of the left foot.

According  to reports, agents of the Atlantic Command, under  the
orders  of  Colonel Walter Monge, dependent of the  Ministry  for
Public  Safety, attacked the families with tear-gas and fire-arms
shooting at waist level.

The  same  stated that the families in question had occupied  for
over  a  year a property called "Finca 18 de Abril S.A..  At  the
beginning  of  May the administrative authorities  ordered  their
eviction  granting them 24 hours to abandon the land. Immediately
afterwards  an  appeal was lodged with the IVth Chamber  tribunal
which declared the eviction order null and void. However, shortly
afterwards the decision of the IVth Chamber was cancelled and the
police proceeded to carry out the eviction without prior notice.

The  peasants  also  allege that during the  events  in  question
various  members  of  the  private police,  called  ASEVIA,  were
present.

CODEHUCA and the Costa-Rican Commisson of Human Rights  -  CODEHU
-
consider that the eviction of these families is an arbitrary  act
because  it  took  place before the exhaustion  of  the  judicial
procedure in the Agrarian Tribunal of Pococ=ED, as well as the non-
intervention  of  the  Institute  for  Agrarian  Development,  as
provided for such cases by the law on land and colonization.

Action requested

Write  to  the Costa-Rican authorities urging them  to  take  the
necessary measures in order to:

i. put  an  end to the illegal or arbitrary actions of the forces
   of  order and ensure that the families concerned are  able  to
   enjoy  the  respect  of their fundamental  liberties  and  the
   rights recognized on their behalf by the law;

ii.carry  out  a  thorough and impartial investigation  into  the
   events          described  above in order  to  identify  those
   responsible   and  impose          upon  them  the   sanctions
   provided by legislation;

iii.     guarantee  that Juan Victor Victor, Rene Rojas  and  the
   other   injured  people  shall  have  access  to  the  medical
   assistance which their state of      health requires, as  well
   as       the       right      to      receive      appropriate
   compensation.

iv.ensure  the  effective respect of human rights and fundamental
   freedoms  throughout the country in accordance  with  national
   laws and international standards.

Addresses :
        S.E.  Ing.  Jose  Maria  Figueres,  Presidente  de  la
Republica, Casa Presidencial, Apartado 100089, San Jose, Costa
Rica.  Telex : 2106 (PRESIDE)   Fax (+506) 227 48 66

       Dr. Juan Diego Castro, Ministro de Seguridad Publica  y
Gobernacion,  Ministerio de Seguridad Publica  y  Gobernacion,
San Jose, Costa Rica.  Fax.: (+506) 253 90 78

     Diplomatic representatives of Costa Rica in your  respective
countries.

Geneva, 10th June 1996

Kindly inform us of any action undertaken quoting the code number
of this appeal in your reply.

--=====================_834588441==_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="VEN10066.ASC"

                          Case VEN 100696

The  International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS-Torture  requests  your
URGENT intervention in connection with the following  situation in
Venezuela.

Brief description of the situation

The  Support  Network  for Justice and  Peace,  a  member  of  our
network,  has expressed its concern for the safety and freedom  of
members  of  the  Committee  for the  Lands  of  Pollire  (in  the
Municipality  of  Zamora, State of Barinas), and particularly  the
following  people  :  Julian  LOPEZ  MORA,  Dario  Alonso  MEDINA,
Baudilio CONTRERAS and Nelson Willian ARIAS, as well as members of
their families.

The  persons  mentioned  above and their families  have  been  the
victims  of threats and harassment on the part of members  of  the
Guardia  Nacional as a reprisal for their complaints  of  acts  of
violence carried out by  agents of the forces of order.

On  16th  November  1995 some 250 Venezuelan families  from  Santa
Barbara,  Municipality of Zamora, State of Barinas and members  of
the  Committee  for Lands of Pollire, occupied waste  lands  which
they  had  requested  the  authorities of  the  National  Agrarian
Institute  and other bodies to let them have for the  previous  14
months.  Up  to that time the authorities had failed to  take  the
necessary steps to grant these persons the right of property  over
part of the lands in question.

On  November 19th 1995 the families mentioned above were  attacked
verbally and physically in an indiscriminatge manner by 70  agents
of  the National Guard under the orders of Capt. Jose Raul Linares
Gonzalez,  Lt.  Porra  (of  the Chururu  frontier  unit)  and  Lt.
Areteaga,  commanding the platoon of the 2nd Company  of  Regional
Detachment  I.  In  the course of these events  many  people  were
detained and were only released after prolonged interrogation.

Action requested :

Please write to the Venezuelan authorities urging them to :

i. take  the  appropriate measures to guarantee the  physical  and
   psychological integrity of Mr Julian Lopez Mora,  Dario  Alonso
   Medina,  Baudilio  Contreras and Nelson  William  Arias,  their
   families and other members of the Pollire Land Committee.

ii.carry  out an impartial and exhaustive investigation  into  the
   facts  described in order to identify those responsible,  bring
   them to trial and apply the appropriate sanctions;

iii.     ensure  in  all circumstances the full respect  of  human
   rights  and  fundamental freedoms in accordance  with  national
   legislation and international standards.

Addresses :

Sr.  Rafael  Caldera,  Presidente  de  la  Republica,  Palacio  de
Miraflores, Caracas, Venezuela. Telex : 21161 MIRAF VC -  Fax :  +
58 2 83 82 39

Dr.  Ruben Creixems Savignon, Ministro de Justicia, Ministerio  de
Justicia,  Torre  Norte, piso 25, Centro Simon  Bolivar,  Caracas,
Venezuela. Telex : 21935 MINJU VC - Fax : + 58 2 482 09 94

Dr.  Ivan  Dario  Badell,  Fiscal  General  de  la  Republica,  La
Candelaria, Caracas, Venezuela. Telex : 24787 EXTER VC

General  Orozco Graterol, Ministro de Defensa Nacional, Ministerio
de  Defensa  Nacional,  Fuerte Tiuna,  Conejo  Blanco,  El  Valle,
Caracas,  Venezuela. Fax : + 58 2 662 8829 (if  voice,  asks:  "me
podria dar tono de fax?").

Dr.  Ramon  Escovar  Salom,  Ministro  de  Relaciones  Interiores,
Ministerio  de Relaciones Interiores, Carmelitas a Santa  Capilla,
Caracas, Venezuela.
Telex : 26429 EXTER VC -  Fax : + 58 2 815 796

NGOs

Oficina  de  los  Derechos Humanos, Vicariato  Apostolico,  Puerto
Ayacucho, Venezuela. Faxes: + 58 48 21721

Geneva, 10 June 1996

Kindly  inform us of any action undertaken quoting the code number
of the present appeal.

