ORGANIZERS: FIND OUT ABOUT DYNAMIC NEW STRATEGIES THAT MOVE BEYOND 
IDENTITY POLITICS.

For what Manning Marable calls "a blueprint for practical, 
community-based organizing and grassroots mobilization, and a 
progressive, multicultural vision of radical democracy," check out John 
Anner's new book, Beyond Identity Politics: Emerging Social Justice 
Movements in Communities of Color (South End Press). E-mail 
south.end.press@lbbs.org for a catalog or review copy. See 
http:\\www.lbbs.org\sep\beyondid.htm for a description of the book and 
