So: U-hr
From: cispesnatl@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: carnet.alerts
Subject: New Death Squad in Salvador -Alert!
Date: 02 Jul 1996 08:39:18 -0800 (PST)

  C     I     S     P     E     S
ACTION ALERT
***************************** Committee in Solidarity with the
People of El Salvador

National Office: P.O. Box 1801, New York, NY 10159 ~ 212-229-1290
3 Regional Offices: Boston, MA 617-524-1166 3 New York, NY
212-229-1290 3  Minneapolis, MN 612-872-0944  3  San Francisco, CA
415-648-6520

e-mail: cispesnatl@igc.apc.org fax: 212 645-6657
******************************* Denounce Surge of New Death Squad
-- "Nationalist Force Major Roberto D'Aubuisson" and Threats
Against Salvadoran Leaders, Media and Free Speech

												June
												27,
												1996

On Wednesday, June 26, 1996, a new death squad appeared calling
itself National Force Major Roberto D'Aubuisson, FURODA. The
clandestine group sent out "Communiqu No. 1" threatening with
death 15 persons including journalists, politicians, and religious
leaders, as well as various media outlets.

The communiqu accuses the members of the opposition of being
"destabilizers . . . that have dedicated themselves to the
destabilization of the administration of President Calderon Sol".
And that they have "abused broad liberties . . . defaming and
taking away prestige of honorable persons including Lic. Juan Jose
Domenech [president of ARENA], Lic. Mario Acosta [Minister of the
Interior], Mr. Tomas Calderon Sol [ARENA leader and brother of the
President], and Businessman Don Hugo Barrera [Minister of Public
Security]."

The communiqu accuses Channel 12, Diario Latino, Radio Sonora,
Radio Maya Vision, and the "ill-fated" foreign press of being
"destabilizing voices." The communiqu lists 15 names of people it
considers "objects" of FURODA, who have "destabilized and sold out
the fatherland." The list includes Auxiliary Bishop of San
Salvador Gregorio Rosa Chavez, the Vice-rector of the UCA, Rodolfo
Cardenal, Human Rights Advocate Victoria de Aviles, FMLN Deputy
Gerson Martinez, Lutheran Bishop Medardo Gomez, Francisco Lima,
former vice-presidential candidate for the FMLN/Democratic
Convergence, FMLN leader Facundo Guardado, Kirio Waldo Salgado of
the Party of Liberty and Democracy, as well as directors and
journalists from the media mentioned above.

The communiqu ends saying, "to all of these worms,
sons-of-bitches, we give notice that your days are numbered and
that you will receive just pay for defending the terrorists that
from the University of El Salvador (UES), continue being
instruments to destabilize El Salvador."

"To the foreign press especially, we give notice that our
sovereign territory does not permit your ill-fated interference.
For every disinformation that you make, our forces will provoke a
sabotage."

In late May, Salvador Snchez Cern, Coordinator of the FMLN,
released to a television station the names of death squad leaders
in Berlin, Usulutn who had recently met in that city.  The group
includes ex-military officers, purged from the army in the peace
process, as well as wealthy business people, landholders and the
current Head of Operations for the Land Bank.

International solidarity must weigh in to denounce the formation
of new death squads and pressure the government to following up on
the work of the Truth Commission and the Joint Group to
investigate and prosecute the death squads.

SUGGESTED ACTIONS:

1. Get your Congressional Representative to call and fax John
Hamilton, Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Latin America
and the Caribbean and to send copies cc: to Anne Patterson, Acting
Assistant Secretary of State for Inter-American Affairs and
Ambassador James Dobbins, Special Assistant to the President for
Latin America at the National Security Council.

Their calls and letters should a) call for an investigation into
these death threats and threats against freedom of the press; b)
express concern over the rise of new death squads; c) demand that
violators be prosecuted and that the recommendations of the Truth
Commission and the Joint Group mandating investigation and
prosecution of the death squads be complied with.  Adopt the
letter attatched to CISPES Action Alert dated 6/19/96

Congressional Switchboard: 202-224-3121

2. Spanish speakers are encouraged to call President Armando
Calderon Sol and express the concerns above.

President Armando Calderon Sol Casa Presidencial San Salvador, El
Salvador Tel: 011-503-271-1555;     Fax: 011-503-271-0950
.
