From: geo@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: dev.humansettl
Subject: Addition to Summer Institute
Date: 03 Jun 1996 19:26:33 -0800 (PST)

For those interested in the recent posting about the Geocommons Summer 
Institute in Sustainable Living and Eco-Village Design, we're excited 
to announce that we've just expanded the program from 6 to 7 weeks to 
include a very special opportunity at a nominal extra charge!

During the last two weeks, Institute students are invited to attend 
the Permaculture Design Course (PDC) of the Institute for Bioregional 
Studies at the site of the original New Alchemy Institute Ark on 
Prince Edward Island, Canada.  This is a very special opportunity to 
be guided by outstanding international faculty in ecological design 
and to cooperatively explore ways to apply new learnings towards 
making one's own campus, community, and home more sustainable.

The new cost for the 7 week Summer Institute is $2,400 including room, 
board, tuition and PDC.  For more information, please contact us at 
geo@igc.org.  Thanks!

