Subject: OMCTFI:SDN06056/arbitrary arrests
Date: 30 May 1996 03:30:43

--=====================_833470523==_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"



--=====================_833470523==_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="iso-8859-1"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="SDN06056.ASC"

                           Case SDN 060596.1
                     Follow-up of Case SDN 060596
                                  and
                          Case SDN 060596.1CC
                    Follow-up of Case SDN 060596.CC
                                  =20
The  International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS Torture has  just  received
new information in the following situation in Sudan.

Brief reminder of the situation:
The  Sudanese  Victims  Of Torture Group, a  member  of  our  network,
informed  the  International Secretariat  of  the  detention,  without
charge,  of  36  detainees at Kober Prison (a list  of  the  names  is
available on request).

As  a  result of the detention, a great number of them were  suffering
from  various  ailments,  such as skin, joint  or  breathing  problems
(asthma).

New information:
According to information received from the Sudanese Victims Of Torture
Group,  4 of the 36 detainees were released on 26 May 1996 : Mr  Elsir
Osman  BABU,  politician; Mr Sir Elkhtim Osman ALHAG,  politician;  Mr
Mutwakil Hag HAMED and Mr Noor Sharaf ELDIN, farmer.

The  other  32 detainees are still in detention, among them Mr  Mohmed
Hussain Ali a 14 year old student.

Actions requested:
Please write to the Sudanese Authorities urging them to:

i.  take  the  appropriate  measures to  guarantee  the  physical  and
    psychological  integrity of Mr Mohmed Hussain Ali  and  order  his
    immediate  release if he is being detained without  valid  charges
    or,  if  such  charges  exist, bring him before  a  competent  and
    impartial  tribunal  for  juvenile  offenders  and  guarantee  his
    procedural rights all times;

ii. take  the  appropriate  measures to  guarantee  the  physical  and
    psychological  integrity  of  all  other  detained   persons   and
    immediately  release  these persons if  they  are  being  detained
    without  valid  charges  or,  if such charges  exist,  bring  them
    before  a  competent  and impartial tribunal and  guarantee  their
    procedural rights all times;

iii.guarantee  a  full,  impartial  and exhaustive  enquiry  into  the
    facts,  concerning  the  supposed illegal  detention  of  all  the
    persons  above mentioned, identify those responsible,  bring  them
    to  trial,  and  apply  the  penal,  civil  and/or  administrative
    sanctions provided by legislation;

iv. ensure   in  all  circumstances  respect  for  human  rights   and
    fundamental  freedoms  in  accordance  with  national   laws   and
    international standards;

Addresses:
His Excellency Lieutenant General Omar Hassan al-Bashir, President  of
the Republic, People=92s Palace, PO Box 281, Khartoum, Sudan.
Telex : 22385 PEPLC SD or 22411 KAID SD - Fax : + 249 11 71 724

Dr.  al-Tayib  Ibrahim Muhammad Kheir, Minister of Interior,  People=92s
Palace, PO Box 281, Khartoum, Sudan. Telex : 22842 WZARA SD or
22604 IPOL SD - Fax : + 249 11 71724 / 73046 / 70186

Mr.=92Abd  al-Aziz  Shiddu,  Minister of Justice  and  Attorney-General,
Ministry of Justice, Khartoum, Sudan. Telex : 22459 KHRJA SD or
22461  KHRJA SD (via Ministry of Foreign Affairs) - Fax : + 249 11  74
063

Mr.  Ali Osman Mohamed Taha, Minister of Foreign Affairs, Ministry  of
Foreign Affairs, PO Box 873, Khartoum, Sudan.
Telex : 22459 KHRJA SD or 22461 KHRJA SD - Fax : + 249 11 74 063

Geneva, 30 May 1996

Kindly  inform  us of any action undertaken quoting the  code  of  the
present appeal in your reply.

