Subject: OMCT:SDN040696/new arrests
Date: 04 Jun 1996 06:25:42

--=====================_833913072==_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"



--=====================_833913072==_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="SDN04066.ASC"

                      Case SDN 040696

The  International Secretariat of OMCT/SOS Torture requests
your  urgent  intervention in the  following  situation  in
Sudan.

Brief description of the situation:
The  Sudanese  Victims of Torture Group, a  member  of  our
network,  has expressed grave concern for the physical  and
psychological  integrity of Mr. Ali  Habeeb  Alla  and  ex-
journalist Mr. Adil Karar.

According to the information received, Mr. Ali Habeeb Alla,
aged  63,  and  Mr.  Adil  Karar, aged  34,  were  arrested
seemingly without charge on 16 May, 1996 and are being held
at  the  "Ghost House" inside Kober prison. Mr. Ali  Habeeb
Alla suffers from asthma and heart disease. SVTG fears that
under  the  circumstances he is being subjected to  torture
and  his  health is deteriorating quickly. Mr.  Adil  Karar
also  suffers from asthma.  It is feared that  neither  are
receiving any kind of medical attention.

Given  the  cases  described in the previous  appeals  (see
cases  SDN 060596, SDN 130596, SDN 140596, and SDN 300596),
OMCT   is   gravely  concerned  for  their   physical   and
psychological integrity.

Actions requested:
Please write to the Sudanese Authorities urging them to:

i.  take   the   appropriate  measures  to  guarantee   the
    physical and psychological integrity of Mr. Ali  Habeeb
    Alla  and Mr. Adil Karar and immediately release  these
    persons  if  they  are  being  detained  without  valid
    charges or, if such charges exist, bring them before  a
    competent  and  impartial tribunal and guarantee  their
    procedural rights at all times;

ii. guarantee  a  full,  impartial, and exhaustive  inquiry
    into the facts, including particularly the practice  of
    torture,  identify  those responsible,  bring  them  to
    trial,    and   apply   the   penal,   civil,    and/or
    administrative sanctions provided by legislation;

iii.ensure  in  all circumstances respect for human  rights
    and  fundamental freedoms in accordance  with  national
    laws and international standards;

Addresses:
His  Excellency  Lieutenant General Omar Hassan  al-Bashir,
President  of the Republic, People's Palace,  PO  Box  281,
Khartoum, Sudan.
Telex : 22385 PEPLC SD or 22411 KAID SD - Fax : +249 11  71
724
Dr.    al-Tayib   Ibrahim  Muhammad  Kheir,   Minister   of
Interior,  People's  Palace, PO Box 281,  Khartoum,  Sudan.
Telex  :  22842 WZARA SD or 22604 IPOL SD - Fax :  +249  11
71724 / 73046 /70186
Mr.   'Abd   al-Aziz   Shiddu,   Minister  of  Justice  and
Attorney-General,  Ministry of  Justice,  Khartoum,  Sudan.
Telex  : 22459 KHRJA SD or 22461 KHRJA SD (via Ministry  of
Foreign Affairs) - Fax : +249 11 74 063
Mr.  Ali  Osman Mohamad Taha, Minister of Foreign  Affairs,
Ministry  of Foreign Affairs, PO Box 873, Khartoum,  Sudan.
Telex : 22459 KHRJA SD or 22461 KHRJA SD - Fax : +249 11 74
063

Geneva, 4 June, 1996

Kindly inform us of any action undertaken quoting the  code
of the present appeal in your reply.

--=====================_833913072==_
